25/02/2007
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- The Sofia Regional Prosecution announced on Saturday (February 24th) that it is investigating an alleged raid the ultra nationalist Attack coalition's leader Volen Siderov and Attack supporters conducted on the editorial offices of the leading newspapers 24 Chasa and 168 Chasa.
According to local media reports, the Attack members arrived at the offices Friday, searching the premises and shouting insults.
The papers had written recently about Attack's funding sources.
Siderov says he only visited the newspapers' headquarters to deliver a written statement to the editors.
(bTV, BNR - 24/02/07)
